error.description: Gets or sets whether or not the text field is in a visually invalid state. This error state overrides the error state controlled by `reportValidity()`.

errorText.description: The error message that replaces supporting text when `error` is true. If `errorText` is an empty string, then the supporting text will continue to show. This error message overrides the error message displayed by `reportValidity()`.

noAsterisk.description: Disables the asterisk on the floating label, when the text field is required.

required.description: Indicates that the user must specify a value for the input before the owning form can be submitted and will render an error state when `reportValidity()` is invoked when value is empty. suffixText.description: An optional suffix to display after the input value.

hasLeadingIcon.description: Whether or not the text field has a leading icon. Used for SSR.

hasTrailingIcon.description: Whether or not the text field has a trailing icon. Used for SSR.

supportingText.description: Conveys additional information below the text field, such as how it should be used.

textDirection.description: Override the input text CSS `direction`. Useful for RTL languages that use LTR notation for fractions.

cols.description: The number of cols to display for a `type="textarea"` text field. Defaults to 20.

maxLength.description: The maximum number of characters a user can enter into the text field. Set to -1 for none. https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input#maxlength

min.description: Defines the most negative value in the range of permitted values. https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input#min

pattern.description: A regular expression that the text field's value must match to pass constraint validation. https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input#pattern

multiple.description: Indicates that input accepts multiple email addresses. https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input/email#multiple

anchor.description: The ID of the element in the same root node in which the menu should align to. Overrides setting `anchorElement = elementReference`. __NOTE__: anchor or anchorElement must either be an HTMLElement or resolve to an HTMLElement in order for menu to open.

quick.description: Skips the opening and closing animations.

hasOverflow.description: Displays overflow content like a submenu. Not required in most cases when using `positioning="popover"`. __NOTE__: This may cause adverse effects if you set `md-menu {max-height:...}` and have items overflowing items in the "y" direction.

open.description: Opens the menu and makes it visible. Alternative to the `.show()` and `.close()` methods

xOffset.description: Offsets the menu's inline alignment from the anchor by the given number in pixels. This value is direction aware and will follow the LTR / RTL direction. e.g. LTR: positive -> right, negative -> left RTL: positive -> left, negative -> right

yOffset.description: Offsets the menu's block alignment from the anchor by the given number in pixels. e.g. positive -> down, negative -> up

noHorizontalFlip.description: Disable the `flip` behavior that usually happens on the horizontal axis when the surface would render outside the viewport.

noVerticalFlip.description: Disable the `flip` behavior that usually happens on the vertical axis when the surface would render outside the viewport.

typeaheadDelay.description: The max time between the keystrokes of the typeahead menu behavior before it clears the typeahead buffer.

anchorCorner.description: The corner of the anchor which to align the menu in the standard logical property style of <block>-<inline> e.g. `'end-start'`. NOTE: This value may not be respected by the menu positioning algorithm if the menu would render outisde the viewport. Use `no-horizontal-flip` or `no-vertical-flip` to force the usage of the value

menuCorner.description: The corner of the menu which to align the anchor in the standard logical property style of <block>-<inline> e.g. `'start-start'`. NOTE: This value may not be respected by the menu positioning algorithm if the menu would render outisde the viewport. Use `no-horizontal-flip` or `no-vertical-flip` to force the usage of the value

stayOpenOnOutsideClick.description: Keeps the user clicks outside the menu. NOTE: clicking outside may still cause focusout to close the menu so see `stayOpenOnFocusout`.

stayOpenOnFocusout.description: Keeps the menu open when focus leaves the menu's composed subtree. NOTE: Focusout behavior will stop propagation of the focusout event. Set this property to true to opt-out of menu's focusout handling altogether.

skipRestoreFocus.description: After closing, does not restore focus to the last focused element before the menu was opened.

defaultFocus.description: The element that should be focused by default once opened. NOTE: When setting default focus to 'LIST_ROOT', remember to change `tabindex` to `0` and change md-menu's display to something other than `display: contents` when necessary.

noNavigationWrap.description: Turns off navigation wrapping. By default, navigating past the end of the menu items will wrap focus back to the beginning and vice versa. Use this for ARIA patterns that do not wrap focus, like combobox.

anchorCorner.description: The anchorCorner to set on the submenu.

menuCorner.description: The menuCorner to set on the submenu.

hoverOpenDelay.description: The delay between mouseenter and submenu opening.

hoverCloseDelay.description: The delay between ponterleave and the submenu closing.

disabled.description: Disables the icon button and makes it non-interactive.

softDisabled.description: "Soft-disables" the icon button (disabled but still focusable). Use this when an icon button needs increased visibility when disabled. See https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/practices/keyboard-interface/#kbd_disabled_controls for more guidance on when this is needed.

flipIconInRtl.description: Flips the icon if it is in an RTL context at startup.

download.description: The filename to use when downloading the linked resource. If not specified, the browser will determine a filename. This is only applicable when the icon button is used as a link (`href` is set).

ariaLabelSelected.description: The `aria-label` of the button when the button is toggleable and selected.

toggle.description: When true, the button will toggle between selected and unselected states

selected.description: Sets the selected state. When false, displays the default icon. When true, displays the selected icon, or the default icon If no `slot="selected"` icon is provided.

type.description: The default behavior of the button. May be "button", "reset", or "submit" (default).

value.description: The value added to a form with the button's name when the button submits a form.

disabled.description: Disables the item and makes it non-selectable and non-interactive.

isMenuItem.description: READONLY: self-identifies as a menu item and sets its identifying attribute

selected.description: Sets the item in the selected visual state when a submenu is opened.

quick.description: Opens the menu synchronously with no animation.

required.description: Whether or not the select is required.

errorText.description: The error message that replaces supporting text when `error` is true. If `errorText` is an empty string, then the supporting text will continue to show. This error message overrides the error message displayed by `reportValidity()`.

label.description: The floating label for the field.

noAsterisk.description: Disables the asterisk on the floating label, when the select is required.

supportingText.description: Conveys additional information below the select, such as how it should be used.

error.description: Gets or sets whether or not the select is in a visually invalid state. This error state overrides the error state controlled by `reportValidity()`.

menuPositioning.description: Whether or not the underlying md-menu should be position: fixed to display in a top-level manner, or position: absolute. position:fixed is useful for cases where select is inside of another element with stacking context and hidden overflows such as `md-dialog`.

clampMenuWidth.description: Clamps the menu-width to the width of the select.

typeaheadDelay.description: The max time between the keystrokes of the typeahead select / menu behavior before it clears the typeahead buffer.

hasLeadingIcon.description: Whether or not the text field has a leading icon. Used for SSR.

displayText.description: Text to display in the field. Only set for SSR.

menuAlign.description: Whether the menu should be aligned to the start or the end of the select's textbox.

get.description: The index of the currently selected option. Note: For SSR, set `[selected]` on the requested option and `displayText` rather than setting `selectedIndex` setting `selectedIndex` will incur a DOM query.
